# Code Review Guidelines — [Project Name]

## Always Check

- New API routes have auth checks
- Database queries use parameterised values (no string interpolation)
- Client components have `"use client"` directive when using hooks/state/effects
- Server actions validate inputs before DB operations
- No hardcoded app name, URLs, or feature flags — use central config
- No raw `<button>`, `<input>`, `<a>` elements — use component library equivalents

## Convention Violations (flag as NIT)

- [Add your project-specific conventions here]
- Example: Raw `<div>` for layout instead of layout components
- Example: CSS variables without proper prefix
- Example: Missing component naming convention

## Skip

- [Add paths to skip during review]
- Example: `temp/` — working files, not production code
- Example: `_generated/` — auto-generated files
- Lock files
